lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_581  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Complexin-1 is present in the presynapse (co-localizing with the synaptic vesicle marker Vglut1) in the Calyx of Held terminal of the MNTB in the brainstem (Fig.1C). Complexin-2 expression is downregulated in Calyx of Held terminals during development (Fig.11). At P21, Vglut-1 immunoreactivity does not colocalize with with Complexin-immunoreactivity in Complexin-1 KO mice (Fig.11C). Therefore, the immunoreactivity in wild-type Calyx of Held terminals at P21 must originate from the presence of Complexin-1 in the presynapse (Fig.1C).\nComplexin-1 immunreactivity is present in the somata of the MNTB principal neurons indicating also a postsynaptic localization.\n\nIHC was performed using an antibody (SySy, rabbit anti-Cplx-1/2) that detects Complexin-1 and -2. Complexin-1 KO mice exhibit a loss of immunoreactivity in the somata of the MNTB principal neurons (Fig 11C) indicating the specificity of the antibody.. Experimental description: Cplx1+/+ and Cplx1-/- littermates of either sex were used for most of the experiments..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_581" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

